main event: An observation of an oblong brilliant white object in Columbus, Ohio on November 16, 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for one minute,The size of the object was compared to a dime at arm's length,The object was noted to be trending northward at a high altitude,The reporting officer concurred that the sighting was likely caused by an aircraft,The conclusion suggested it was probably a balloon, but there was insufficient data for a full evaluation.
